Kpler's Ritolia believes the decline in India's Russian oil purchases won't have much of an impact on its import bill or global oil prices because a "trade shuffle" will occur."China will buy that Russian oil which India won't, and for that it will have to let go of some other market, maybe The Middle East, which India would buy from. The Dubai pricing complex will get a bit of a premium."The larger concern for the oil market, analysts say, is the possibility of a U.S. and Iran conflict.

